Numeric Pain Rating Scale (NPRS): Measures pain intensity on a scale of 0 to 10.
https://www.physio-pedia.com/Numeric_Pain_Rating_Scale

McGill Pain Questionnaire (MPQ): Assesses pain quality using descriptive words.
https://www.sralab.org/sites/default/files/2017-07/McGill%20Pain%20Questionnaire%20%281%29.pdf

Neuropathic Pain Scale (NPS): Assesses pain intensity of a scale of 0 to 10 for neuropathic pain.
https://www.mdcalc.com/calc/3626/neuropathic-pain-scale-nps

Brief Pain Inventory (BPI): Measures pain severity and its interference with daily functions. 
http://www.npcrc.org/files/news/briefpain_short.pdf

Central Sensitization Inventory (CSI): Determines whether patients have the presence of central sensitization. 
https://www.physiotutors.com/questionnaires/central-sensitization-inventory-csi/

Oswestry Disability Index (ODI): Measures disability related to lower back pain.
https://spinesportscare.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Modified-Oswestry-Low-Back-Pain-Disability-Questionnaire.pdf

Roland-Morris Disability Questionnaire (RMDQ): Assesses functional disability from back pain. Typically used for research 
https://mississaugahalton.rehabcareontario.ca/Uploads/ContentDocuments/Roland-Morris-Questionaire.pdf

Oswestry Disability Index (ODI): Measures disability related to neck pain. 
https://drcynthiasmith.com/storage/app/media/_FORMS/new_forms/oswestry-neck-form.pdf

Disabilities of the Arm, Shoulder And Hand Questionnaire (DASH): Measures the ability of your upper extremities.
https://healthcare.msu.edu/_assets/documents/lymphedema/DASH-questionnaire.pdf

Lower Extremity Functional Scale (LEFS):  Asks about very specific functions your legs do.
https://www.emoryhealthcare.org/-/media/Project/EH/Emory/ui/pdfs/msk-pt-forms/hip-lefs.pdf

Fibromyalgia Impact Questionnaire (FIQ): Evaluates the overall impact of fibromyalgia. 
https://static.medicine.iupui.edu/divisions/rheu/content/physicians/FIQ_scoring_1103b.pdf

Western Ontario and McMaster Universities Arthritis Index (WOMAC): Measures pain, stiffness, and function in arthritis patients.
https://www.princetonhcs.org/-/media/files/forms/princeton-rehabilitation/womac.pdf

Kaiser Permanente Scoliosis Spine Questionnaires(KPSSQ): Built for scoliosis however this is a great example of the questions we will be asking
https://mydoctor.kaiserpermanente.org/ncal/Images/Scoliosis%20Spine%20Questionnaires_revised_ADA_tcm75-682768.pdf

National Headache Foundation Migraine Disability Index: Built for Migraines and Headaches
https://headaches.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/MIDAS.pdf

Pelvic Girdle Questionnaire (PGQ): People with Pelvic Girdle Pain during pregnancy and postpartum.
https://www.physio-pedia.com/Pelvic_Girdle_Questionnaire_(PGQ)

Knee Injury and Osteoarthritis Outcome Score (KOOS): Measures pain, stiffness, and functional impairment in knee injuries and osteoarthritis.
https://www.aaos.org/globalassets/quality-and-practice-resources/patient-reported-outcome-measures/lower-extremities/koos.pdf

Shoulder Pain and Disability Index (SPADI): Assesses pain and disability related to shoulder conditions.
https://denalipt.com/wp-content/uploads/Shoulder-Pain-and-Disability-Index.pdf

Patient-Specific Functional Scale (PSFS): Allows patients to identify and rate activities most affected by their condition.
https://www.sralab.org/sites/default/files/2017-06/Patient-specific.pdf

Fear-Avoidance Beliefs Questionnaire (FABQ): Examines how fear and avoidance contribute to chronic pain.
https://www.tac.vic.gov.au/files-to-move/media/upload/fear_avoidance.pdf

Pain Catastrophizing Scale (PCS): Measures thoughts and feelings related to pain catastrophizing.
https://www.oregon.gov/oha/HPA/dsi-pmc/PainCareToolbox/Pain%20Catastrophizing%20Scale.pdf

Tampa Scale for Kinesiophobia (TSK): Assesses fear of movement and reinjury.
https://novopsych.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/tsk-tampa-scale-of-kinesiophobia.pdf

Pain Self-Efficacy Questionnaire (PSEQ): Assesses confidence in performing activities despite pain.
https://novopsych.com.au/assessments/health/pain-self-efficacy-questionnaire-pseq/

Short Form-36 (SF-36): A general quality-of-life assessment tool.
https://clinmedjournals.org/articles/jmdt/jmdt-2-023-figure-1.pdf

Pain and Sleep Questionnaire (PSQ): Evaluates the impact of pain on sleep quality.
https://www.med.upenn.edu/cbti/assets/user-content/documents/Perceived%20Stress%20Questionnaire%20(PSQ).pdf

Multidimensional Pain Inventory (MPI): Evaluates psychological and social aspects of pain.
https://www.sralab.org/sites/default/files/2017-07/west_haven_yale_multidimensional_pain_inventory.pdf

Chronic Pain Acceptance Questionnaire (CPA):: Measures acceptance of chronic pain and its impact.
https://www.div12.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Chronic-Pain-Acceptance-Questionniare-Revised.pdf

Brief Multidimensional Life Satisfaction Scale (BMLSS): Evaluates overall life satisfaction, including health and functionality.
https://sc.edu/study/colleges_schools/artsandsciences/psychology/documents/huebner_brief_lifesatisfaction_scale.pdf

